	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I don't see why this would be such a shock for people, since this sort of thing already has been done on the NES before (e.g. <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BCzzgjdH0JU" class="postlink">glitchNES</a>).
<br />It's also been done <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3hGVFFiRDJ0&amp;feature=player_detailpage#t=29s" class="postlink">on the Megadrive</a>. And there are mods for the DMG/GBC that allow you to achieve various glitch effects.
<br />
<br />Some people like this sort of stuff. It's intentional. It's not always as simple as it might look to the viewer.
<br />Move on.

		

		</td>
