	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hi. I'm the creator of this demo. Thanks for the interesting polarized conversation and analysis. The demo is exactly as intended: when my video player just wasn't ready for the Assembly party competitions, I decided to use it as is and found really interesting emergent glitches on the real hardware, so I explored different ways of fucking up the decompression routine. Emulators are unusable in this nature as they cannot reliably reproduce the incorrect PPU behaviour. Oh, and it's coded in C.

		

